  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 400
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/soy-redcurrant-lamb-stir-fry-5ce5367173c4810017453bba
servings: 2
cuisine: Asian
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 
a pinch of @salt{} for the noodles. Chop the @broccoli{1}(cut into florets) into 
florets (like small trees!). Lay them on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} 
and season with a pinch of salt and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then roast on the 
top shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once roasted, remove from 
the oven and leave to the side.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). 
Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). 
Peel and grate the @ginger{1%thumb-sized piece}(peeled and grated). Trim the 
@carrot{1}(trimmed, halved lengthways and sliced into half moons).

Place the @egg noodle nests{2} into the pan of boiling water, stir to separate 
and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back into the 
pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and mix through to stop them sticking together. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the 
@lamb strips{200%g} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir-fry until browned on 
the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once browned, remove the strips to a #bowl{}. Put 
the pan back on the heat and turn the heat to medium-high. Add the onion and 
carrot along with another drizzle of oil if needed, and a pinch of salt and 
pepper. Stir-fry until the onion and carrot have softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the ginger and garlic to the pan and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}, then add lamb 
strips back into the pan and remove the pan from the heat. Add the 
@redcurrant jelly{25%g} and the @soy sauce{25%ml} along with 1 tbsp of @water{2%tbsp} 
per person. Stir together to dissolve the jelly, then add the roasted broccoli 
and noodles into the pan and toss everything together.

> IMPORTANT: The lamb strips are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Pop back on the heat and warm everything through until piping hot, about ~{2%minutes}. 
Remove from the heat. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. 
Serve in bowls. Enjoy!